_:Nfa8e59e36d1249419a16cc8326fecdee <http://schema.org/name> "George Mpanga" .
_:Nfa8e59e36d1249419a16cc8326fecdee <http://schema.org/description> "<p>George Mpanga was born to Ugandan parents on the St Raphael’s Estate in Neasden, north-west London and began performing rap and grime when he was 15 years old.</p>\n\n<p>He attended Queen Elizabeth’s School, Barnet, an elite selective grammar school, during 2002 to 2009.</p>\n\n<p>He subsequently studied politics, psychology and sociology at King’s College, Cambridge (2010 to 2013), where he decided to adapt his rap output into poetry to communicate more effectively with his audience.</p>\n\n<p>In November 2014, it was announced that he had been shortlisted for the Critics’ Choice category at the 2015 BRIT Awards.</p>\n\n<p>In March 2018 it was announced that he had been elected as a Member of the National Council of Arts Council England.</p>\n" .
